# Technical Development Rules

## Code Architecture
- **SOLID Principles**: Apply SOLID principles to all code
- **Separation of Concerns**: Keep different responsibilities separate
- **Dependency Injection**: Use dependency injection for testability
- **Interface Segregation**: Prefer interfaces over concrete classes

## Unreal Engine Best Practices
- **UCLASS Usage**: Proper UCLASS macro usage with appropriate specifiers
- **Memory Management**: Understanding of UE garbage collection
- **Asset Loading**: Use Asset Manager for asynchronous loading
- **Performance**: Profile and optimize performance-critical code

## Code Quality Standards
- **Naming Conventions**: Follow UE naming conventions consistently
- **Documentation**: All public APIs must be documented
- **Error Handling**: Proper error handling and logging
- **Code Reviews**: All code changes require review

## Testing Requirements
- **Unit Tests**: Core systems must have unit tests
- **Integration Tests**: System interactions must be tested
- **Performance Tests**: Critical paths must be performance tested
- **Regression Tests**: Bug fixes must include regression tests